  <div class="item">
          <a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/brainstorm-green-2013"><img width="180" height="69" src="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/bsg-homepage.png" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="bsg-homepage" /></a>
    <h4><a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/brainstorm-green-2013">Brainstorm Green 2013</a></h4>
    <h5>April 29-May 1, 2013: Laguna Niguel, CA</h5>
    <p>Top environmentally-minded business leaders and the green movement's brightest thinkers will convene in Laguna Niguel, California on April 29-May 1, 2013 for <em>Fortune</em> magazine's sixth Brainstorm GREEN conference.</p>
    <a href="brainstorm-green-2013/brainstorm-green-registration" class="register">Register </a>  </div>
    
  <div class="item">
          <a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/global-forum-2013"><img width="100" height="100" src="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/2012_FGF_Logo_FIN_squreRED1.gif" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="2012_FGF_Logo_FIN_squreRED" /></a>
    <h4><a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/global-forum-2013">Global Forum 2013</a></h4>
    <h5>6-8 June 2013: Chengdu, People’s Republic of China</h5>
    <p>The Global Forum is returning to China in 2013 for the fourth time, more than any other country. The Forum convenes the chairmen, presidents, and CEOs of the world’s largest companies on the dynamic frontiers of international commerce. Participation is by invitation only.</p>
    <a href="global-forum-2013/global-forum-registration" class="register">Register </a>  </div>
    
  <div class="item">
          <a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/brainstorm-tech-2013"><img width="180" height="65" src="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/brainstorm-tech-logo.gif" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="brainstorm-tech-logo" /></a>
    <h4><a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/brainstorm-tech-2013">Brainstorm TECH 2013</a></h4>
    <h5>July 22-24, 2013: Aspen, Colorado</h5>
    <p>In 2013, <em>Fortune</em>'s technology, media, and Internet editorial talent will again bring together a distinguished group of top technology, entertainment, and media thinkers and doers, along with entrepreneurs, innovators, business visionaries and influencers to discuss the new technologies and ideas changing our rapidly evolving world.</p>
    <a href="brainstorm-tech-2013/brainstorm-tech-registration" class="register">Register </a>  </div>
    
  <div class="item">
          <a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/most-powerful-women-2013"><img width="95" height="95" src="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/mpw-homepage-logo.gif" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="mpw-homepage-logo" /></a>
    <h4><a href="http://www.fortuneconferences.com/most-powerful-women-2013">Most Powerful Women Summit 2013</a></h4>
    <h5>October 15-17, 2013: Washington, D.C.</h5>
    <p>The MPWSummit is the world's premiere gathering of women leaders in business, government, academia, philanthropy, and the arts. Each fall, a select group comes together to exchange big ideas and learn. The program — no speeches! — is diverse and designed to facilitate energetic and provocative conversation. Participation is by invitation only. 
</p>
    <a href="most-powerful-women-2013/most-powerful-women-summit-registration" class="register">Register </a>  </div>
    
